e 2: Named Queues**\n- Support multiple independent named queues\n- Default queue when no name given\n- List all queue names\n- Backward compatible with Phase 1\n\n**Phase 3: Priority**\n- Priority levels 1-10 (1=highest, 5=default)\n- Higher priority first, then FIFO\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Validate priority values\n\n**Phase 4: Delayed/Scheduled Tasks**\n- Delay in ms or specific future time\n- Not returned until availability time passes\n- Ordering: available tasks > delayed tasks not yet available\n- When multiple become available: by time, then priority, then FIFO\n\n**Phase 5: Retry with Backoff**\n- Mark tasks as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks re-added with exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt-1)`\n- Default 3 retries, configurable\n- Default 1000ms base delay, configurable\n- Track attempt count\n- Exhaust retries → failed state\n\n**Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue (DLQ)**\n- Failed tasks moved to per-queue DLQ\n- View all dead-lettered tasks\n- Move dead-lettered tasks back to original queue\n- Clear DLQ for a queue\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n**Phase 7: Task Dependencies**\n- Specify task IDs that must complete first\n- Blocked tasks not returned\n- Check unblocked when dependency completes\n- Detect circular dependencies at creation time\n- Depending on non-existent task → error\n- Failed dependency doesn't fail dependents (they stay blocked)\n- Inspect dependency status\n\n**Phase 8: Concurrency Control**\n- Per-queue max concurrent processing limit\n- At limit → return null even if pending tasks available\n- Complete/fail task → frees slot\n- Default: unlimited\n- Set/query concurrency limit and active count\n- Respects priority ordering under concurrency limit\n\n**Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation**\n- Report progress as percentage (0-100) with optional message\n- Query task progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates\n- Unsubscribe capability\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending → removed from 