+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011Vm1ARq6SmQXkQZSmCh4tV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n     2→\n     3→Add the ability to shut down the task queue system in an orderly fashion.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- A shutdown operation should signal the system to stop accepting new tasks.\n     8→- After shutdown is initiated, attempting to add new tasks should produce an error.\n     9→- The shutdown should wait for all currently-processing tasks to finish, up to a configurable timeout.\n    10→- If processing tasks do not complete within the timeout, they should be force-cancelled.\n    11→- Callbacks can be registered to run during the shutdown process.\n    12→- The shutdown should produce a summary indicating how many tasks completed, how many were force-cancelled, and how long the shutdown took.\n    13→- Calling shutdown multiple times should be safe and return the same result.\n    14→- If no tasks are processing, shutdown should complete immediately.\n    15→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01151BgFhXJBL59kF6yioaZo","session_id":"a4530823-757f-4daf-bdef-7f93fba6cecb","uuid":"5c50bbc6-619e-471d-9852-3284a1b60ef6"}
